        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Sync device data back to host if dirty, then free device memory</para>
<para>Leaves with the host side marked dirty, so a .device/.device_const call in a future <ref refid="classamrex_1_1AMReX" kindref="compound">AMReX</ref> session resyncs to device. A dirty marked device side remains authoritative even when it was shrunk to size zero through the mutable device vector returned by device().</para>
<para>Assumes the GPU context is still alive (called from ExecOnFinalize, which runs before GPU device teardown in <ref refid="namespaceamrex_1a8117ae9942e01445ea7fe62d2f190c64" kindref="member">amrex::Finalize</ref>). </para>
        </detaileddescription>
